{"annotations": [{"id": ["NCBITaxon:7955"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "Zebrafish", "obj": "species", "prob": 0.8697605133056641, "span": {"begin": 67, "end": 76}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:196"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "Ahr", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9938238859176636, "span": {"begin": 127, "end": 130}}, {"id": ["mesh:D002318"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "cardiovascular", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.6295084953308105, "span": {"begin": 182, "end": 196}}, {"id": ["mesh:D010490"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "pericardial edema", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.996566653251648, "span": {"begin": 220, "end": 237}}, {"id": ["mesh:D013749"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "TCDD", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9996050000190735, "span": {"begin": 392, "end": 396}}, {"id": ["CHEBI:31204"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "PAH", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9798760414123535, "span": {"begin": 405, "end": 408}}, {"id": ["mesh:D001564"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "Benzo[a]pyrene", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9995094537734985, "span": {"begin": 410, "end": 424}}, {"id": ["mesh:D020111"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "Aroclor 1254", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9994314908981323, "span": {"begin": 470, "end": 482}}, {"id": ["mesh:C023035"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "PCB-126", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9981749057769775, "span": {"begin": 501, "end": 508}}, {"id": ["mesh:C108338"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "cyprodinil", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9986268281936646, "span": {"begin": 553, "end": 563}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:196"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "Ahr", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9950318336486816, "span": {"begin": 744, "end": 747}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:196"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "Ahr", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9914167523384094, "span": {"begin": 826, "end": 829}}, {"id": ["mesh:D066126"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "cardiotoxicity", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.8282061815261841, "span": {"begin": 846, "end": 860}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:196"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "Ahr", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9796220064163208, "span": {"begin": 880, "end": 883}}], "text": "Empirical evidence and essentiality of KEup for KEdown to occur    Zebrafish embryos exposed during development to a number of Ahr activating chemicals cause concentration-dependent cardiovascular toxicity, indicated as pericardial edema (area, severity, or percent animals), inhibition of cardiac looping, among other cardiac-specific measurements. Examples include, but are not limited to, TCDD and the PAH, Benzo[a]pyrene (Bugiak and Weber 2010; Knecht et al. 2017), Aroclor 1254 (Li et al. 2014), PCB-126 (Jonsson et al. 2007; Liu et al. 2016), and cyprodinil (Tang et al. 2020).     Additionally, several morpholino knockdown (Jayasundara et al. 2015; Jonsson et al. 2007) and CRISPR-Cas9 knockout (Fu et al. 2019) studies, in addition to Ahr chemical inhibitor (McGee et al. 2013) studies have definitively demonstrated Ahr&rsquo;s role in cardiotoxicity induced by several Ahr activating chemicals.", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 15:48:22 +0000 2026"}